<p>Hello <%= @first_name %> <%= @last_name %>,</p>

<p>You are getting this email because you are the primary contact for <%= @business_name %>.</p>

<p>The new CleanBC Better Homes Energy Savings Program contractor portal is ready!</p>

<p>Program registered contractors must transfer their accounts to the new portal.  
<strong>If you do not transfer the account, you cannot submit invoices or get paid.</strong></p>

<p>Transferring the account should take less than 5 minutes.</p>

<p>To make it easier, there is a unique link below that transfers the primary contact and business details. 
Past submissions are not transferred.</p>

<p>The link will not expire but you should create your account as soon as you can. 
You can only use the link once to transfer the account. 
If someone else uses the link after the account is transferred, they will get an error message.</p>

<p><strong>You cannot submit invoices in the old contractor portal after March 10, 2026.</strong></p>

<p>Follow the steps below to transfer your account.</p>

<p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; border-bottom: 2px solid #333; padding-bottom: 4px; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 8px;">Before you start</p>

<p>You need a <a href="#">Business BCeID</a> account for your company. You cannot log into the new portal with your old login credentials.<br>
Make sure you know your Business BCeID manager account log in information.</p>

<p style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Employee portal access</p>

<p>Any employee that submits invoices must use their own Business BCeID user account to log in.</p>
<ul>
  <li>You create user accounts for employees from the Business BCeID manager account</li>
  <li>For step-by-step instructions, use the <a href="#">Business BCeID Account Management Guide</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Do not share BCeID accounts between employees.<br>
For BCeID help <a href="#">contact the Service BC help desk</a></p>

<p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; border-bottom: 2px solid #333; padding-bottom: 4px; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 8px;">How to transfer your contractor account</p>

<p style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Step 1 &ndash; Open new portal with the link below and log in</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="#">Open the new contractor portal using this link</a></li>
  <li>Log in with your Business BCeID account</li>
</ul>

<p style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Step 2 &ndash; Accept terms and conditions</p>
<ul>
  <li>Review and accept the terms and conditions for using the new portal</li>
</ul>

<p style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Step 3 &ndash; Create account and explore the portal</p>
<ul>
  <li>Click create account</li>
  <li>Access the portal and review program resources</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>The last day you can submit invoices in the old portal is March 10, 2026.</strong></p>

<p><a href="<%= @root_url %>welcome/contractor/invite?token=<%= @token %>" target="_blank">Log in to the new Contractor Portal</a></p>

<p>Thank you,<br>Energy Savings Program Support</p>

<p>Have questions or need help?</p>
<p>Contact us at <a href="mailto:ESPcontractorsupport@clearesult.com">ESPcontractorsupport@clearesult.com</a></p>
